[SN]TITLE[SN]
Culinary delight from India's Bihar state

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Litti chokha is one of the most popular street foods in India.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
22 July 2016 Last updated at 00:27 BST
Litti are chargrilled flavour bombs, especially when freighted with chokha, the spicy stew of grilled aubergine, tomato and potato.
The BBC's Justin Rowlatt tastes this mouth-watering street food from the eastern Indian state of Bihar.
Filmed and edited by Sanjay Ganguly
